<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 13 at 8:23PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Randolph
County through 900 PM CDT...
At 822 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Roanoke, moving north at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke, Wedowee, Woodland, Morrison Cross Roads, Crystal Lake,
Graham, Dickert, Newell, Napoleon, Tennant, Rock Mills, Big Springs,
Paran, Roanoke Municipal Airport and Rock Stand.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
